        <p>
          The quality of beef depends on the feeding of the animal,
          the age at which it is slaughtered, and the handling of the meat.
          We raise high quality antibiotic and hormone free Angus beef.
          Our animals are range-fed on grass, finished on grain, and slaughtered at 12 to 18 months.
          Since we have our own processing plant, there is no trauma associated in loading the animals
          and shipping them to a slaughter house.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our beef cuts have bright pink-red flesh, light-colored bones, and creamy-white fat.
          In texture, it has fine flesh, soft-looking bones, and crumbly suet or exterior fat.
          It has a delicate network of fat running through the flesh.
          This is the "marbling" which dissolves during cooking, providing aromatic internal basting.
        </p>
        <p>
          The ground beef has less then 20% fat.
          After grinding, it is immediately air sealed and frozen.
          This method ensures our hamburger is the freshest and best testing.
        </p>
        <p>
          Beef is good, beef is great, beef is better on your plate!
        </p>
